ial groups in Estonia, Latvia and Lithuania.\n* {{Cite book\n| last1 = Smith\n| first1 = David James\n| last2 = Pabriks\n| first2 = Artis\n| last3 = Purs\n| first3 = Aldis\n| last4 = Lane\n| first4 = Thomas\n| author2-link = Artis Pabriks\n| title = The Baltic states: Estonia, Latvia and Lithuania\n| year = 2002\n| publisher = Routledge\n| location = London\n| isbn = 0-415-28580-1\n| url = https://books.google.com/?id=YaYbzQQN97EC&pg=PA24\n| page = 24\n| ref=harv\n}}\n* {{Cite book\n| last = Subrenat\n| first = Jean-Jacques\n| author-link = Jean-Jacques Subrenat\n| title = Estonia: identity and independence\n| url = https://books.google.com/?id=kBZlHdp7tdcC\n| year = 2004\n| publisher = [[Rodopi (publisher)|Rodopi]]\n| location =\n| isbn = 90-420-0890-3\n| ref=harv\n}} [https://www.questia.com/PM.qst?a=o&d=111478379 online edition]\n* Taagepera, Rein. ''Estonia: Return to Independence'' (Westview Press, 1993) [https://www.questia.com/PM.qst?a=o&d=51017789 online edition]\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|History of Estonia}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20050905022125/http://www.einst.ee/publications/hip/ Estonian History in Pictures], an Estonian Institute publication\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20080304100811/http://www.baltische-ritterschaften.de/Englische%20Version/index-engl.htm Association Of Baltic German Knighthoods]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20070621094523/http://www.historycommission.ee/temp/conclusions.htm Crimes against humanity during Soviet and German occupation of Estonia]\n*[http://www.hoeckmann.de/germany/baltics.htm Historical maps of Estonia in the 16th, 17th and 18th century]\n*[http://www.mois.ee/english/history.shtml History of Estonian Manors], part of English version of the Estonian Manors Portal\n*[http://www.theeuropeanlibrary.org/portal/libraries/Libraries.php?launch=1&language=en&page=Treasures&country=Estonia Cultural treasures National Library Estonia]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20190310213950/http://www.ce-review.